类 Pawn

java.lang.Object
structure.Cell
structure.Pawn
所有已实现的接口:
PawnPromotion
public class Pawn
extends Cell
implements PawnPromotion
This is the subclass Pawn which extends the abstract class Cell. The Pawn class implements the movement of Pawn piece on the board.

  • 构造器详细资料

    • Pawn

      public Pawn​(java.lang.String cellName, java.lang.String pieceName, boolean isAlive, int x, int y)
      Initialize the Pawn object with cellName, pieceName, isAlive, x, y.
      参数:
      cellName - The cell's name, such as "##" or " ",which is under the Pawn piece.
      pieceName - The Pawn piece's name, such as "wR" or "bR".
      isAlive - The boolean value to show whether the piece is alive on the board.
      x - The x-coordinate of the piece on the board.
      y - The y-coordinate of the piece on the board.

  • 方法详细资料

    • Ownside

      public boolean Ownside​(java.lang.String name1, java.lang.String name2)
      This method judge if the piece named "named2" is on the same side of the piece named name2
      参数:
      name1 - The piecename of the first piece
      name2 - The piecename of the second piece
      返回:
      if they are on the same side, then return true. Otherwise, false.

    • Enpassant

      public boolean Enpassant​(java.lang.String currName, int currX, int currY, int tarX, int tarY)
      This method is to judge if the pawn on (currX,currY) can use enpassant to (tarX,tarY)
      参数:
      currName - the name of the piece
      currX - The current x-coordinate of the piece
      currY - The current y-coordinate of the piece
      tarX - The target x-coordinate of the piece
      tarY - The target y-coordinate of the piece
      返回:
      If the pawn in (currX,currY) can move to (tarX,tarY) by en-passant, then true. Otherwise, false

      public boolean move​(int currX, int currY, int tarX, int tarY)
